  "prompt": "What mean by alkali?",
  "response": "An alkali, also known as a base, is a chemical substance that has the following key characteristics:\n\n1. Chemical properties:\n- Produces hydroxide ions (OH-) when dissolved in water\n- Neutralizes acids\n- Has a pH greater than 7\n- Feels slippery or soapy to the touch\n\n2. Common examples:\n- Sodium hydroxide (NaOH)\n- Potassium hydroxide (KOH)\n- Calcium hydroxide (Ca(OH)2)\n- Ammonia (NH3)\n- Baking soda (sodium bicarbonate)\n\n3. Common uses:\n- Soap production\n- Cleaning products\n- Industrial chemical processes\n- Neutralizing acidic substances\n- Regulating pH in various applications\n\n4. In general chemistry:\n- Accepts protons (H+ ions)\n- Reacts with acids to form salt and water\n- Conducts electricity when dissolved in water\n\n5. Physical characteristics:\n- Usually soluble in water\n- Typically metallic compounds\n- Can be corrosive in concentrated forms\n\nAlkalis play crucial roles in many chemical and biological processes and have wide-ranging applications in industry and everyday life.",
